<font color="#FF0000">YOU CAN RELATE TO THIS...</font><br>
<tt>Thu Nov 28  0:37:03 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
To Brett Michaels:<br><br>
I was in college at the time of the war, and watched many <br>
friends go oversea and a fair number never return. One of the<br>
single-most tangible reasons for you to be able to relate is<br>
your right to vote.  At the time of the Vietnam War, youngsters<br>
who had no rightful say in governmental affairs served their<br>
country and gave their lives.  The fact that you gained the<br>
right to vote at 18 is a privelege that I believe many young<br>
folks do not yet appreciate, and sadly squander.  Admittedly, <br>
Vietnam and Watergate have destroyed much of our faith in our<br>
elected leaders and the political process, but the right to<br>
vote and to align your voice with those similar in thought<br>
is far too precious to waste.  I hope you are and will con-<br>
tinue to be an active citizen.  God knows the future of our<br>
country depends on it!
